<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Air3" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Air,</orth> subst., a piece of music, played or sung, and chiefly one adapted to words: <cit><quote>a wonderful sweet a., with admirable rich words to it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 3, 19</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>this music . . . with its sweet a.,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.393" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 393</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.58.393" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.4" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.183" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 183</bibl> <cit><quote>(your tongue's sweet a.) any a. of music,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 5.76" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 76</bibl></cit>. Plural: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.422" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 422</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.2.145" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.4.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 4, 5</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>